<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1014" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1014">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/2697</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Lithuanian National
                                        Council</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-18"><hi rend="italic">November 18,
                                        1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: The Department has received your
                                communication of November 14 and has the honor to inform you that
                                the points which are raised in the communication relative to the
                                aspirations for Lithuanian independence have been carefully noted
                                and will receive due consideration in connection with similar
                                questions which will require attention in negotiations for a general
                                peace which will prove lasting.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                    <persName><hi rend="smallcaps">William
                                    Phillips</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>